    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Numerical integration (midpoint rule) converges at rate O(1/n^2). The upper/lower sum approach converges at O(1/n) for monotone functions. Neither is the Riemann integral itself: that is the common value they converge to. The FTC proof requires the mean value theorem, not computation.</p>

